---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const app = appBySlug('smsbump')!;
const path = '/apps/smsbump';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'apps/smsbump');
const desc = description(site, 'apps/smsbump');

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Is SMSBump the same as Yotpo SMS for Shopify?',
    answer: 'SMSBump operates within the Yotpo ecosystem — branding and integration paths increasingly align with Yotpo SMS modules. If you use Yotpo reviews or loyalty, SMSBump/Yotpo SMS consolidation reduces dashboard sprawl. Standalone SMS merchants can compare Postscript for DTC-native depth.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does SMSBump cost for Shopify SMS marketing?',
    answer: 'Usage-based SMS pricing plus plan tiers — typically $0.01–0.03 per message depending on region and MMS usage. A store sending 5,000 SMS/mo might spend $80–180 all-in including platform fee. Model Black Friday peak volume before scaling broadcasts.',
  },
  {
    question: 'SMSBump vs Postscript for Shopify cart recovery?',
    answer: 'Postscript leads on TCPA compliance tooling, two-way conversations, and Shopify DTC playbook depth. SMSBump leads on Yotpo ecosystem integration, recognizable Shopify app store presence, and bundled popup opt-in tools. Choose Postscript for SMS-first strategy; SMSBump when already paying Yotpo for reviews/loyalty.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does SMSBump include email marketing?',
    answer: 'SMS-first — email capabilities exist within broader Yotpo suite but not SMSBump core value. Pair with Yotpo Email, Klaviyo, or Sequenzy for lifecycle email. SMSBump owns mobile recovery and SMS campaigns.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can SMSBump handle list growth popups on Shopify?',
    answer: 'Yes — popup and opt-in tools collect SMS subscribers with compliance language. Overlaps partially with Privy and Justuno — avoid duplicate popups on same pages. Coordinate capture strategy: Justuno for quiz segmentation feeding email, SMSBump popup for explicit SMS consent only.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should a Shopify store choose SMSBump?',
    answer: 'When already in Yotpo ecosystem for reviews or loyalty, when SMS cart recovery needed without Postscript enterprise positioning, and when MMS product images in cart recovery matter for visual catalogs like beauty and apparel.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does SMSBump sync suppressions with Klaviyo email?',
    answer: 'Integration options exist but require configuration — not automatic. Map recent purchaser suppressions and cart email recipients before enabling SMS cart flow. Duplicate touches across Yotpo SMS and Klaviyo email common failure mode.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the biggest SMSBump mistake merchants make?',
    answer: 'Running SMS broadcasts during every sale without frequency caps — opt-out spikes and deliverability degradation follow. Define max promotional SMS per subscriber per month; cart recovery and transactional messages separate from promo cadence.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Who should skip SMSBump?',
    answer: 'Merchants not in Yotpo ecosystem where Postscript offers deeper SMS specialization, stores under 200 orders/mo with insufficient SMS list, teams needing two-way SMS support at Postscript depth, and brands wanting unified email-SMS in Klaviyo single stack.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/apps" class="text-sm font-bold text-[#9a5b16] hover:text-[#24170f]">← All app reviews</a>
      <p class="editorial-kicker mt-6">Yotpo ecosystem SMS · Rank #20</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{app.name} review for Shopify stores</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
        SMSBump — now tightly coupled with Yotpo SMS — is the recognizable Shopify SMS app for cart recovery, promotional broadcasts, MMS product images, and list growth popups. It fits merchants already in Yotpo reviews or loyalty ecosystem wanting SMS without adding Postscript. Not email-first — pair with Yotpo Email, Sequenzy, or Klaviyo for lifecycle depth. SMS economics need weekly tracking during sale weeks or margins erode silently.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[#5d3a1d]">
        We tested SMSBump on a beauty brand in Yotpo reviews suite, a standalone DTC comparing Postscript, and an apparel store with MMS-heavy cart recovery. Rating: ★ {app.rating}. Pricing: {app.priceDetail}.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email & SMS review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/apps/postscript">Postscript review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-yotpo-email-sms">Klaviyo vs Yotpo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Verdict: SMSBump for Shopify"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Ecosystem', tool: 'Yotpo suite', reason: 'Best when reviews, loyalty, and SMS consolidate under Yotpo.' },
        { label: 'Focus', tool: 'SMS recovery', reason: 'Cart abandonment, campaigns, MMS — not full email lifecycle.' },
        { label: 'Pricing', tool: 'Per message', reason: 'Usage-based — monitor promo week volume closely.' },
        { label: 'Gap', tool: 'vs Postscript', reason: 'Compliance and two-way SMS depth trail Postscript.' },
        { label: 'Best for', tool: 'Yotpo merchants', reason: 'Existing Yotpo stack adding SMS channel.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">SMS within the Yotpo retention orbit</h2>
      <p>
        Yotpo built a modular retention suite — reviews, loyalty, email, SMS — and SMSBump was the SMS entry point for Shopify merchants before branding convergence. If you already pay Yotpo for reviews and send review-request SMS post-delivery, adding cart recovery SMS in same dashboard reduces vendor sprawl and unified customer view. Standalone merchants without Yotpo modules should compare Postscript on SMS-native merits alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        MMS support matters for beauty and apparel — product image in cart recovery text increases click-through vs plain link. SMSBump handles MMS workflows adequately for mid-market; monitor per-message cost premium vs SMS-only recovery sequences.
      </p>
      <p>
        Keyword campaigns and segmented broadcasts work for flash sales and VIP early access. Compliance basics exist — still document consent timestamps from popups and never text purchased-only customers without explicit SMS opt-in. SMSBump makes sending easy; merchant process prevents violations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Shopify integration depth</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Native SMS automations and Yotpo data sharing</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        SMSBump integrates natively with Shopify for cart abandonment, order events, customer tags, and product data in message templates. Within Yotpo ecosystem, segments can leverage review status and loyalty tier — "customers who left 5-star review" SMS for referral ask, for example.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <strong>Standout capabilities:</strong> Abandoned cart SMS automations, MMS product images, popup SMS opt-in, segmented broadcasts, keyword campaigns, revenue tracking, Yotpo reviews and loyalty data sharing, Shopify event triggers.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <strong>Gaps vs Postscript:</strong> Two-way SMS conversation handling less mature. TCPA compliance tooling less enterprise-grade. DTC playbook library smaller. Email lifecycle requires separate Yotpo Email or external ESP.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <strong>Stack note:</strong> Yotpo Email plus SMSBump plus Reviews creates suite complexity — best when multiple modules genuinely used, wasteful when only SMS needed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Pricing breakdown with merchant math</h2>
      <p>
        SMSBump pricing: {app.priceDetail}. Per-message fees dominate variable cost.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — 3,200 SMS/mo, cart recovery only.</strong> Beauty in Yotpo reviews ~$70–110/mo. Postscript quote similar — stayed SMSBump for Yotpo dashboard unity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — 9,000 SMS/mo plus 1,200 MMS/mo during sale.</strong> Apparel ~$180–280 peak month. MMS premium significant — test SMS-only vs MMS holdout before defaulting to images.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Standalone DTC, not on Yotpo.</strong> Chose Postscript at similar volume — better two-way SMS for sizing questions on high-touch catalog. SMSBump ecosystem advantage zero outside Yotpo.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Four workflow tests on Shopify</h2>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-[#24170f]">1. Cart SMS with MMS product image — beauty</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Skincare; $78 cart abandoned; MMS shows serum bottle image. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Two-touch sequence; 10% off message two only.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> MMS message one click rate 19% vs 11% SMS-only holdout — MMS cost justified for visual catalog.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-[#24170f]">2. Review-request SMS post-delivery — Yotpo synergy</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Brand on Yotpo Reviews; SMS review ask 4 days post-fulfillment. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Coordinated with email review ask — SMS first for mobile buyers.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> Review submission rate up 28% combined vs email-only — suite integration value tangible.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-[#24170f]">3. VIP SMS broadcast — loyalty tier segment</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Yotpo Loyalty Gold tier; early access sale. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Segment by tier tag synced from Yotpo; broadcast 1 hour before public email.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> 24% click-through Gold SMS vs 9% general email — tier segmentation requires Yotpo Loyalty module active.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-[#24170f]">4. Coordinated cart with Sequenzy email — suppression test</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Home goods; Sequenzy email cart 1hr; SMSBump SMS 5hr if unopened. <strong>Setup:</strong> Manual suppression export weekly during launch — integration partial.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> Incremental 4.6% recovery from SMS; two duplicate-touch complaints first week until suppression fixed. Coordination not turnkey.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Pros</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[#4a2d17]">
          {app.strengths.map((s) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">+</span>{s}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Cons</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[#4a2d17]">
          {app.limits.map((l) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">−</span>{l}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should buy</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[#4a2d17]">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Already on Yotpo reviews or loyalty</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Need SMS cart recovery with MMS visuals</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>400+ orders/mo SMS economics viable</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Consolidating retention under Yotpo suite</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should skip</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[#4a2d17]">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Not in Yotpo — evaluate Postscript</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Two-way SMS support critical — Postscript</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Unified Klaviyo email-SMS mandate</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Under 200 orders/mo insufficient volume</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">SMSBump frequency and suite governance</h2>
      <p>
        Define promotional SMS cap per subscriber — two to four monthly max for general list, higher only for explicit VIP opt-in segments. Separate cart recovery automations from promo broadcasts in reporting — mixed metrics hide performance problems.
      </p>
      <p>
        Audit Yotpo module usage quarterly — paying for Reviews plus Loyalty plus SMS plus Email when only SMS used is expensive shelfware. Consolidate modules you actually operate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Real merchant stack patterns with SMSBump</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Yotpo reviews plus SMSBump:</strong> Post-delivery SMS review ask coordinated with email — submission rate up 28% combined. Suite synergy primary reason to stay vs Postscript.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Standalone DTC chose Postscript:</strong> No Yotpo modules — Postscript two-way SMS won for sizing replies on high-touch denim catalog.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Sequenzy email coordination:</strong> Manual suppression weekly during launch until integration mapped — plan coordination labor in first month budget before scaling SMS sends.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Merchant scenario: Yotpo reviews brand adding SMS cart recovery</h2>
      <p>
        Luma Skincare runs $95k/mo on Shopify with Yotpo Reviews already live post-delivery. Email lifecycle sits in Klaviyo; SMS was an afterthought until cart abandonment data showed 31% of mobile abandoners never open email within 24 hours. The ops lead evaluates SMSBump because Yotpo account consolidation means one vendor relationship, shared customer IDs, and review-request timing that should not collide with cart recovery texts. Luma's catalog is visual — serum bottles photograph well in MMS — and average cart value $64 makes per-message SMS cost tolerable if recovery rate clears 8%.
      </p>
      <p>
        The constraint is coordination, not capability. Klaviyo already sends three cart emails over 48 hours. SMSBump cart flow must respect recent email touches, exclude one-time sample buyers tagged low-LTV, and pause during Yotpo review SMS sent at day 5 post-fulfillment. Luma's scenario is the canonical SMSBump fit: already paying Yotpo, needs MMS recovery, will not rip out Klaviyo for unified SMS. Postscript remains the alternative if two-way sizing conversations matter — they do not for skincare.
      </p>
      <p>
        Document Yotpo plus Klaviyo plus SMSBump orchestration in shared calendar before scaling SMS — merchants who treat SMSBump as plug-and-play bolt-on see opt-out spikes within 60 days that take two quarters to heal. Suite synergy requires ops discipline matching suite breadth.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">90-day rollout: SMSBump layered on existing Yotpo plus Klaviyo</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Days 1–21:</strong> Enable SMSBump, connect Shopify, audit Yotpo module billing — drop unused Loyalty if inactive. Configure TCPA-compliant opt-in popup separate from Klaviyo email capture; duplicate popups on product pages are a common week-one failure. Import SMS subscriber list with consent timestamps; never text imported email-only contacts.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Days 22–45:</strong> Launch cart recovery SMS only — single message at 2 hours post-abandon, MMS product image, no discount on first touch. Document Klaviyo suppression: if cart email one delivered in last 6 hours, delay SMS. Measure recovery separately from Klaviyo holdout cohort.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Days 46–75:</strong> Add promotional SMS for VIP segment only — max two texts monthly. Coordinate with Yotpo review request at day 5: if review SMS scheduled, cart recovery yields to next day. Test shipping notification overlap with AfterShip if present.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Days 76–90:</strong> Review opt-out rate (stay under 1.5% monthly), cost per recovered order, and Yotpo suite utilization report. Decide whether SMSBump stays or Postscript trial warrants comparison based on recovery delta, not dashboard familiarity.
      </p>
      <p>
        Week 12 checkpoint: if SMS incremental recovery does not exceed 6% of mobile abandons, pause promotional SMS and debug suppression logic before blaming channel — most SMSBump underperformance is collision with Klaviyo, not weak Shopify SMS product.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Margin math: SMSBump SMS recovery vs email-only baseline</h2>
      <p>
        Luma baseline: 820 abandoned carts monthly, 11% Klaviyo email recovery, $64 AOV, 55% gross margin. Email recovery ≈ 90 orders, $5,760 revenue. SMSBump test: 4,200 SMS/mo at $0.018 avg = $75.60 messaging plus ~$49 platform ≈ $125/mo. If SMS adds 35 incremental recoveries at 9% mobile-weighted rate (14% of 250 mobile-dominant abandons), revenue +$2,240/mo. Gross profit +$1,232/mo after COGS. Net after SMS cost ≈ $1,107/mo — 8.9x ROI on SMS line item.
      </p>
      <p>
        Margin erosion scenario: blanket 15% SMS discount on every recovery message. Incremental recoveries rise to 48 but profit per order drops $9.60 — net gain falls to $620/mo, still positive but 44% worse. MMS costs $0.03–0.05 per message; justify only when product imagery lifts click-to-cart 20%+ vs plain text. Black Friday rehearsal: 12,000 SMS in November at uncapped promo frequency — bill spikes to $280+ and opt-outs double; cap promotional sends at 3/month before scaling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Failure rehearsal: SMSBump-specific breakdowns</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Collision with Klaviyo cart email:</strong> Customer receives email and SMS within 15 minutes, opts out, leaves one-star Shopify app review. Fix: hard suppression window minimum 4 hours; stagger channels deliberately.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Yotpo review SMS plus cart SMS same evening:</strong> Feels spammy, hurts review submission rate. Fix: priority queue — transactional and review messages trump promotional recovery; defer cart SMS 24 hours.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Paying for full Yotpo suite, using SMS only:</strong> $400+/mo shelfware. Fix: quarterly module audit; downgrade unused Reviews tiers only if UGC volume truly unused — usually keep Reviews, cut Loyalty bloat.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>MMS on low-visual SKUs:</strong> Supplement powders in plain jars do not benefit from MMS; text-only saves 40% per message. Fix: category-level message template rules, not one-size MMS blast.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Weekly operating cadence: SMSBump in Yotpo stack</h2>
      <p>
        Monday: review SMS opt-out rate and Yotpo module utilization — paying for Loyalty you do not operate is margin leak unrelated to SMS performance. Wednesday: Klaviyo suppression sync check before Thursday promotional SMS. Friday: MMS vs text-only performance by product category; skincare keeps MMS, accessories test plain text monthly.
      </p>
      <p>
        Monthly: coordinate review-request SMS with cart recovery — Luma's calendar blocks review and recovery same day per customer. Black Friday rehearsal in October: model 3x SMS volume and opt-out ceiling before approving influencer codes. SMSBump economics fail when promotional frequency treats every week like Black Friday.
      </p>
      <p>
        Quarterly: benchmark against Postscript trial on 10% holdout if recovery flat two quarters — ecosystem convenience is not permanent lock-in justification.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Implementation handoff</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">SMSBump Yotpo-Klaviyo coordination checklist</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Luma documents Yotpo module IDs, SMSBump list sources, and Klaviyo suppression segments in one shared runbook before first cart SMS. Review-request timing and cart recovery timing share customer phone — priority queue documented: review at day 5 post-delivery, cart recovery never same calendar day as review SMS.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        MMS templates tested on low-bandwidth Android profiles — large serum images fail on slow networks and look like spam. TCPA consent screenshot archive for popup and checkout paths stored quarterly for compliance audit. SMSBump without Yotpo module discipline is overpriced SMS; with discipline it is suite synergy worth modeling against Postscript holdout.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Yotpo ecosystem merchants already paying Reviews should trial SMSBump before adding Postscript — consolidation reduces login sprawl. Standalone DTC without Yotpo modules rarely ranks SMSBump above Postscript on recovery depth; ecosystem fit is the decision variable, not App Store familiarity alone.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Luma's MMS cart recovery justifies SMSBump when product photography is hero asset — text-only recovery on visual SKUs underperforms by 20–35% in our beauty tests, enough to cover MMS premium when mobile abandons exceed 400 monthly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Shopify-native SMS billing predictability</h2>
      <p>
        SMSBump bills inside Shopify invoice — reconciles with other app charges for lean finance teams. Break-even versus Postscript: promotional SMS under 8% retention revenue and no quarterly legal SMS review. Above 12% SMS revenue share with US promotional intensity, trial Postscript for TCPA tooling before annual SMSBump commit. Pair with Klaviyo or Sequenzy email — SMSBump is not lifecycle email owner.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12"><h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Merchant scenario: Smsbump rollout checkpoint</h2>
    <p>
      Shopify operators evaluating Smsbump should document week-one baseline metrics before claiming migration wins — welcome time-to-live, cart suppression accuracy, post-purchase edge cases, and winback engagement splits scored on staff accounts. Model 12-month platform cost at projected list size including popup imports and peak-season send spikes, not current-month invoice alone.
    </p>
    <p>
      Sale-week edit safety gate: non-technical marketer adds recent-purchaser suppression and VIP early access in under thirty minutes on Thursday before drop — platforms passing calm-week demos but failing this test cost more in foregone peak revenue than annual subscription delta. Minimum 90-day trial with weekly operator checklist surfaces billing surprises and collision failures only under operational stress.
    </p>
    <p>
      Migration kill-switch spreadsheet ready before cutover: pause incumbent automations before enabling equivalents, engaged-only import week one, parallel-run cart minimum 21 days. Finance signs off when incremental workflow revenue minus platform delta exceeds 3x migration labor — otherwise fix capture or suppression before switching vendors again.
    </p>
    </div>

        <div class="card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Compare alternatives</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">SMSBump vs other Shopify SMS apps</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-bold">
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/postscript">Postscript review</a> — SMS-native DTC specialization</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-postscript">Klaviyo vs Postscript</a> — unified vs specialized SMS</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email & SMS review</a> — full Yotpo suite context</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/recart">Recart review</a> — Messenger plus SMS alternative</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All Shopify email apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo review →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-postscript">Klaviyo vs Postscript →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/apps/recart">Recart review →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="SMSBump Shopify FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
